{
    "question_text": "<h3>Valid Parentheses</h3><p>Given a string <code>s</code> containing just the characters <code>'('</code>, <code>')'</code>, <code>'{'</code>, <code>'}'</code>, <code>'['</code> and <code>']'</code>, determine if the input string is <b>valid</b>.</p><p>An input string is valid if:</p><ul><li>Open brackets must be closed by the same type of brackets.</li><li>Open brackets must be closed in the correct order.</li><li>Every close bracket has a corresponding open bracket of the same type.</li></ul>",
    "difficulty": "EASY",
    "marks": 5,
    "input_format": "A single string containing only parenthesis characters.",
    "output_format": "Print \"true\" if the string is valid, else \"false\".",
    "constraints": [
        "1 <= s.length <= 10^4",
        "s consists of parentheses only '()[]{}'."
    ],
    "explanation": "We use a stack. For every opening bracket, we push the corresponding expected closing bracket onto the stack. For every closing bracket, we check if the stack is empty (unmatched closing) or if the top of the stack does not match (wrong type). If either condition fails, return false. After processing all characters, the string is valid only if the stack is empty (all openings have been matched). O(N) time, O(N) space.",
    "answer": "def solve(s):\n    stack = []\n    mapping = {')': '(', '}': '{', ']': '['}\n    for c in s:\n        if c in mapping:\n            if not stack or stack[-1] != mapping[c]: return False\n            stack.pop()\n        else:\n            stack.append(c)\n    return len(stack) == 0",
    "boilerplate": {
        "python": "import sys\n\ndef solve(s):\n    stack = []\n    mapping = {')': '(', '}': '{', ']': '['}\n    for c in s:\n        if c in mapping:\n            if not stack or stack[-1] != mapping[c]: return False\n            stack.pop()\n        else:\n            stack.append(c)\n    return len(stack) == 0\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    s = sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    print(str(solve(s)).lower())",
        "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <string>\n#include <stack>\nusing namespace std;\n\nbool solve(string s) {\n    stack<char> st;\n    for (char c : s) {\n        if (c=='('||c=='['||c=='{') st.push(c);\n        else {\n            if (st.empty()) return false;\n            char top = st.top(); st.pop();\n            if ((c==')' && top!='(')||(c==']' && top!='[')||(c=='}' && top!='{')) return false;\n        }\n    }\n    return st.empty();\n}\n\nint main() {\n    string s;\n    if (getline(cin, s)) cout << (solve(s) ? \"true\" : \"false\") << endl;\n    return 0;\n}",
        "java": "import java.util.*;\npublic class Main {\n    public static boolean solve(String s) {\n        Deque<Character> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();\n        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {\n            if (c=='('||c=='['||c=='{') stack.push(c);\n            else {\n                if (stack.isEmpty()) return false;\n                char top = stack.pop();\n                if ((c==')' && top!='(')||(c==']' && top!='[')||(c=='}' && top!='{')) return false;\n            }\n        }\n        return stack.isEmpty();\n    }\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);\n        if (sc.hasNextLine()) System.out.println(solve(sc.nextLine().trim()));\n        sc.close();\n    }\n}",
        "javascript": "const fs = require('fs');\nfunction solve(s) {\n    const stack = [], map = {')':'(', ']':'[', '}':'{'};\n    for (const c of s) {\n        if ('([{'.includes(c)) stack.push(c);\n        else { if (!stack.length || stack[stack.length-1] !== map[c]) return false; stack.pop(); }\n    }\n    return stack.length === 0;\n}\nconst s = fs.readFileSync(0, 'utf8').trim();\nif (s) console.log(solve(s));",
        "c": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <string.h>\n#include <stdbool.h>\nbool solve(char* s) {\n    char stack[10001]; int top = -1;\n    for (int i = 0; s[i]; i++) {\n        char c = s[i];\n        if (c=='('||c=='['||c=='{') stack[++top]=c;\n        else {\n            if (top<0) return false;\n            char t = stack[top--];\n            if ((c==')'&&t!='(')||(c==']'&&t!='[')||(c=='}'&&t!='{')) return false;\n        }\n    }\n    return top == -1;\n}\nint main() {\n    char buf[10001];\n    if (fgets(buf, sizeof(buf), stdin)) {\n        buf[strcspn(buf,\"\\n\")]=0;\n        printf(\"%s\\n\", solve(buf) ? \"true\" : \"false\");\n    }\n    return 0;\n}"
